Package org.batfish.dataplane.protocols

package org.batfish.dataplane.protocols contains a group of helper classes and functions that implement logic specific to a given routing protocol.

See: Description

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    BgpProtocolHelper  
    GeneratedRouteHelper
    Contains helper logic for manipulating GeneratedRoute objects in the context of dataplane computation.
    IsisProtocolHelper
    Helper class that implements various IS-IS protocol logic.
    OspfProtocolHelper
    Helper class with functions that implement various bits of OSPF protocol logic.
    StaticRouteHelper
    Helper functions implementing logic related to handling of static routes

Package org.batfish.dataplane.protocols Description

package org.batfish.dataplane.protocols contains a group of helper classes and functions that implement logic specific to a given routing protocol. This logic should be re-usable across different dataplane engines
